<span id="freeTextContainer7116740225863421589">This is my third Tayari Jones novel and her writing feels like truth. Messy, uncomfortable, and ultimately beautiful. I appreciate how undone she leaves her endings: loose and pulsing with life. She reminds me of Toni Morrison.</span>

          </span>
